question.text: Which one of the following is incorrect statement?

options.text: The site of actual diffusion of gases between blood and atmospheric air is called exchange part of lungs.
Inspiration is initiated by the contraction of diaphragm and internal inter-costal muscles.
A healthy man inspire or expire approximately 6000 to 8000 ml of air per minute.
About 97 percent oxygen is transported by RBC in the blood.

solution.text: Inspiration is initiated by the contraction of diaphragm and external inter-costal muscles. Due to this the diaphragm flattened to increase volume of thoracic chamber anterio-posterior and ribs pulled outward to increase thoracic volume dorso-ventrally.
